## Title
Pluggable Notification and Review Channels

## Recommendation Summary

### Intent Assessment
Documents the channel-agnostic architecture of the qualification pipeline. Telegram is just one conduit; web UI, CLI, email, Obsidian, and API are equally valid.

### Categorization Changes
- **ZETT**: "none (status: qualifying)" → "content_stage: evergreen" (Architectural insight about channel-agnostic design. Original thinking — evergreen. Missing content_stage field.)
- **TREE**: "meta/tools, meta/pkm" → "meta/beestgraph/architecture, meta/workflows/pipelines" (This is beestgraph architecture about pipeline design. meta/tools is too generic.)
- **GRAPH**: "Likely has Document node" → "Ensure edges to Qualification Pipeline, Mobile Qualification Review Page, Telegram as Capture Source, BKS. Pluggable Architecture and Channel Agnostic should be Concept nodes." (Architecture doc should connect to all channels it describes.)

### Metadata Issues
Missing content_stage field. Status qualifying — could be published. Missing created_at/updated_at. The channel support table with status column (Built/Planned/Future/Works now) is a nice tracking artifact. Related field duplicates Connections — consolidate.

